rved by Reid & Parker (2006). Since most of\nthese PNe come from single or non-interacting binary stars in our model, this\nmeans that most such stars produce PNe contrary to the \"Binary Hypothesis\"\nwhich suggests that binary interaction is required to produce a PN.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Thu, 12 Apr 2012 08:08:45 GMT"}],"update_date":"2015-06-04"}
